msgstr ""

#: ../../api/jinwu.lightcurve.TriggerDecider.rst:19:<autosummary>:1
#: jinwu.lightcurve.trigger.TriggerDecider.sliding_window:1 of
msgid ""
"Scan all windows of size `window` (seconds) and return whether SNR>=7 is "
"achieved, with diagnostic info."
msgstr ""

#: ../../api/jinwu.lightcurve.TriggerDecider.rst:21
msgid "Methods Documentation"
msgstr ""

#: jinwu.lightcurve.trigger.TriggerDecider.cumulative_from_t0:1 of
msgid ""
"Grow cumulatively from T0 and search for the first time SNR>=target. If "
"max_window is given, only search within [T0, T0+max_window)."
msgstr ""

#: jinwu.lightcurve.trigger.TriggerDecider.decide:1 of
msgid ""
"Two-step decision: 1) Sliding `window` SNR anywhere >= target? If yes, "
"trigger. 2) Head `window` SNR >= target? If yes, trigger. 3) Else grow "
"cumulatively from T0 until reach target or series ends. Returns a dict "
"with decision and diagnostics."
msgstr ""

#: jinwu.lightcurve.trigger.TriggerDecider.from_events:1 of
msgid ""
"Bin photon arrival times into counts per bin of width dt. If "
"t_start/t_end are not given, they are inferred from min/max events with "
"one bin padding on the right edge."
msgstr ""

